---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="Every Day Statistics is written by one person, free, for anyone who wants to protect themselves from statistical manipulation."
>
  <div class="eds-main eds-main--narrow">

    <header class="eds-pageheader">
      <div class="eyebrow">About this site</div>
      <h1>One person. <em>No agenda.</em></h1>
    </header>

    <article class="prose eds-prose">
      <p class="lede">
        Every Day Statistics is written by one person, in their evenings, for free, because
        watching ordinary people get talked into bad decisions by bad numbers is exhausting
        and mostly preventable.
      </p>

      <p>
        I'm not a statistician by trade. I'm someone who got tired of reading headlines that
        were technically true and practically misleading, and who realised that the move being
        pulled was almost always the same handful of moves. So I started writing them down.
      </p>

      <p>
        The site isn't a course. It's a kit. Read the 44 units in order — they take about ten
        weeks at fifteen minutes a day — and after that the reference library is here for
        whenever you need to remember the name of a thing.
      </p>

      <h2>What this site won't do</h2>
      <p>
        It won't tell you what to think about any specific issue. It will give you the tools to
        read the numbers attached to that issue, and form your own view, and notice when
        someone is hoping you won't.
      </p>

      <blockquote>
        The point isn't to make you suspicious of every number. It's to make you suspicious of
        the right ones.
      </blockquote>

      <h2>How it's funded</h2>
      <p>
        It isn't. There are no ads, no affiliate links, no sponsors, no paid newsletter. The
        hosting is minimal and I pay it. If that ever changes I'll say so on this page, in
        plain language, before it happens.
      </p>
    </article>

  </div>
</Base>
